            h2 This is demo code
            
            p This game bases on <a href="http://nodejs.org/">Node.js</a> and uses   
                | the <a href="http://expressjs.com">express</a> web development framework,
                | the <a href="https://github.com/visionmedia/jade/blob/master/Readme.md">Jade</a> template engine,
                | the <a href="http://learnboost.github.com/stylus/">Stylus</a> CSS engine and
                | <a href="http://socket.io/">Socket.IO</a> for WebSocket communictation.
            
            p The client-side rendering utilizes CopperLicht 3D, a JavaScript WebGL libraray from <a href="http://www.ambiera.com">Ambiera</a>. 
                | Your browser has to support <a href="http://www.khronos.org/webgl/">WebGL</a> to generate interactive 3D graphics.
                | This game was tested with the latest version of Chrome and Firefox.
                | We recommend Chrome for a smooth gameplay.
            
            p SolarTournament is 100% free and open source software.<br />
                | Why don't you just go to <a href="https://github.com/JohannesHoppe/SolarTournament">GitHub</a> and fork it?!
